<topic id="topic_et">
   <title>Indented Text</title>
   <body>
      <p outputclass="phase2">Indented text is also marked with the <codeph>@rendition</codeph> attribute, which is embedded in the <codeph>&lt;hi&gt;</codeph> element or a block element of the DTA element selection. The position of the text is transmitted as a value of the <codeph>@rendition</codeph> attribute: </p>
      <table>
         <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colname="col1"/>
            <colspec colname="col2"/>
            <thead>
               <row>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col1" nameend="col1">Attribute Value Pair</entry>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col2" nameend="col2">Meaning</entry>
               </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
               <row>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col1" nameend="col1">
                     <codeph>rendition="#et"</codeph>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col2" nameend="col2">indented text</entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col1" nameend="col1">
                     <codeph>rendition="#c"</codeph>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col2" nameend="col2">centered</entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col1" nameend="col1">
                     <codeph>rendition="#right"</codeph>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="0" namest="col2" nameend="col2">right-aligned</entry>
               </row>
            </tbody>
         </tgroup>
      </table>
      <note type="notice"><i><b>Alternative regulation phase 1:</b> Indented text is tagged with the <codeph>&lt;hi&gt;</codeph> element. The position of the text is transmitted in the <codeph>@rendition</codeph> attribute as one of the above-mentioned values.</i></note>
      <p>Indentations and centerings in headings, lists and tables are generally not tagged separately in the DTA corpus. Texts captured using OCR are an exception. </p>
      <note type="attention">In the following example, in addition to indented text, there are various other formattings (i. e. spaced letters, bold, right-aligned).</note>
      <example>
         <title>Indentation</title><fig>
            <image href="img/LsJVxtnwNz.png"/>
            <codeblock outputclass="language-xml">&lt;p&gt;
   &lt;hi rendition="#et #g"&gt;Heidelberg,&lt;/hi&gt; den 15. Juli 1892.&lt;/hi&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;lb/&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
   &lt;hi rendition="#right #b"&gt;E. Kraepelin.&lt;/hi&gt;&lt;/hi&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;lb/&gt;</codeblock>
            <p><i>Source: <xref
               href="http://www.deutschestextarchiv.de/kraepelin_arzneimittel_1892/14"
               format="html" scope="external">Kraepelin, Emil: Ueber die Beeinflussung
               einfacher psychischer Vorg√§nge durch einige Arzneimittel. Jena, 1892.
               [Facsimile 14]</xref>
            </i></p>
         </fig></example>
   </body>
